trans-unit.source: A collection of <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> objects.
A <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection> object contains <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo> objects that represent user profiles from a data source.

A <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection> is returned from the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.GetAllProfiles%2A>, <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.GetAllInactiveProfiles%2A>, <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.FindProfilesByUserName%2A>, and <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.FindInactiveProfilesByUserName%2A> methods of a <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider>.

A <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection> can be supplied to the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.DeleteProfiles%2A> method to delete profile information and properties from the data source.
Creates a new, empty <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref>.

A <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection> is constructed by profile provider implementers and returned from the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.GetAllProfiles%2A>, <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.GetAllInactiveProfiles%2A>, <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.FindProfilesByUserName%2A>, and <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.FindInactiveProfilesByUserName%2A> methods of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider> abstract class.
Adds the specified <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> object to the collection.

The <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection.Add%2A> method is commonly used by profile-provider implementers to populate a <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection> to return from the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.GetAllProfiles%2A>, <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.GetAllInactiveProfiles%2A>, <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.FindProfilesByUserName%2A>, or <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider.FindInactiveProfilesByUserName%2A> method of the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileProvider> abstract class.
A <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> object to add to the collection.
The collection is read-only.
A object with the same value as profileInfo already exists in the collection.
profileInfo is `null`.
-or-
The property of profileInfo is `null`.
Removes all <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> objects from the collection.
The collection is read-only.
Copies the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref> to a one-dimensional array.
This method uses <xref:System.Collections.ArrayList.CopyTo%2A?displayProperty=fullName> to copy <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo> objects to the specified <xref:System.Array>.
A one-dimensional <xref href="System.Array"></xref> that is the destination of the elements copied from the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Array"></xref> must have zero-based indexing.
The zero-based index in array at which copying begins.
Copies the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref> to a one-dimensional array of type <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref>.
This method uses <xref:System.Collections.ArrayList.CopyTo%2A?displayProperty=fullName> to copy <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo> objects to the specified array.

A one-dimensional array of type <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> that is the destination of the elements copied from the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref>.
The array must have zero-based indexing.
The zero-based index in the array at which copying begins.
Gets the number of <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> objects in the collection.
The number of <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> objects in the collection.
Gets an enumerator that can iterate through the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref>.
Enumerators only allow reading the data in the collection.
Enumerators cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
For more information, see <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator>.
An <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> for the entire <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref>.
Gets a value indicating whether the profile info collection is thread safe.
Application code does not normally use this property.
Always `false`, because thread-safe profile info collections are not supported.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> object in the collection, referenced by the specified <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo.UserName"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo.UserName"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> object to retrieve from the collection.
A <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> object for the specified user name.
If name is not found in the collection, `null` is returned.
Removes the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> object with the specified user name from the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo.UserName"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo"></xref> object to remove from the collection.
The collection is read-only.
Makes the contents of the <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref> read-only.

The <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection.SetReadOnly%2A> method marks the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection> as read-only so that <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfo> objects cannot be added to or removed from the collection.
After calling the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection.SetReadOnly%2A> method, you cannot change the <xref:System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection> back to read/write.
Gets the synchronization root.
Application code does not normally use this property.
Always `this` (`Me` in Visual Basic), because synchronization of <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileInfoCollection"></xref> objects is not supported.
